WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:34.560
As-salamu alaykum wa rahmatullahi wa barakatuh.

00:00:34.560 --> 00:00:50.190
بسم الله الرحمن الرحيم. الحمد لله رب العالمين وبه نستعين ونصلي ونسلم على أفضل الخلق أجمعين نبينا محمد وعلى آله وصحبه والتابعين ومن تابعهم بإحسان إلى يوم الدين وبعد.

00:00:50.190 --> 00:00:59.190
We commence by praising Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam, sending blessings and salutations upon Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam, his entire household and all his companions.

00:00:59.190 --> 00:01:02.190
May Allah bless them and may He bless every single one of us.

00:01:02.190 --> 00:01:05.190
Beloved brothers and sisters in Islam,

00:01:05.190 --> 00:01:13.190
We thank Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam for giving us this opportunity to engage in prayer and in salah in this month of Ramadan

00:01:13.190 --> 00:01:20.190
and to be fasting for His sake, abstaining from food and drink and permissible sexual desires.

00:01:20.190 --> 00:01:30.190
And at the same time all this for the sake of Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam whilst being conscious of what we utter during the daylight and the night of the month of Ramadan

00:01:30.190 --> 00:01:35.190
in a way that not only will we be able to achieve the pleasure of Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:01:35.190 --> 00:01:43.190
but we will be able to exit this month of Ramadan in a manner that we become better people than we were before the month.

00:01:43.190 --> 00:01:45.190
May Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam grant us benefit.

00:01:45.190 --> 00:01:56.190
Yesterday we had commenced the battle of Badr, the first major battle that took place between the kuffar of Quraysh and the Muslims from Madinatul Munawwara.

00:01:56.190 --> 00:02:05.190
And we had made mention of some very very important points, the run up to the battle as well as the beginning, the starting point of the battle.

00:02:05.190 --> 00:02:08.190
I d like to just recap very briefly.

00:02:08.190 --> 00:02:15.190
The Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam had a little command center built for him known as Al-Arish.

00:02:15.190 --> 00:02:22.190
And as I said up to today if you were to go to Badr you would find a masjid in the place where this command center was.

00:02:22.190 --> 00:02:32.190
And he had instructed the believers with instructions that people had not yet witnessed before that particular war.

00:02:32.190 --> 00:02:43.190
One of those instructions was that they were to make lines, literally stand in rows just like our rows when we stand up for prayer and salah.

00:02:43.190 --> 00:02:50.190
And thereafter those who were with bows and arrows had to be in the front.

00:02:50.190 --> 00:02:53.190
Those who were with swords had to be behind.

00:02:53.190 --> 00:02:56.190
And as you know they were only two horsemen from amongst them.

00:02:56.190 --> 00:03:07.190
And the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam told them look we had not intended to have this war but seeing that we are going to fight we need to be careful how many spears and arrows we use.

00:03:07.190 --> 00:03:09.190
We don't even have so many.

00:03:09.190 --> 00:03:14.190
And as for the kuffar they were very excited they had been partying the whole evening.

00:03:14.190 --> 00:03:23.190
And there is a narration very clear cut authentic narration that makes mention of the fact that shaitan came to them.

00:03:23.190 --> 00:03:32.190
And shaitan told them on that day of Badr that you will not lose I am with you and I am the one who is going to help you and so on.

00:03:32.190 --> 00:03:34.190
So in what form did shaitan come?

00:03:34.190 --> 00:03:37.190
In the form of a man known as Suraqah bin Malik.

00:03:37.190 --> 00:03:43.190
I'm sure you've heard the name before if you recall when Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam was making the Hijra.

00:03:43.190 --> 00:03:50.190
This Suraqah bin Malik shaitan used to come in his form more than once he has come in the form of this man may Allah protect us.

00:03:50.190 --> 00:03:54.190
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness we don't want the devils coming in our forms.

00:03:54.190 --> 00:04:00.190
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us inshallah the protection against the devil at all times.

00:04:00.190 --> 00:04:08.190
So shaitan came and shaitan promised them that look I am with you you will definitely win there is no chance that those people can win.

00:04:08.190 --> 00:04:16.190
And then when the two armies had finally clashed shaitan saw the angels Jibreel and Mikael.

00:04:16.190 --> 00:04:25.190
The angels were from amongst those who had come down in their thousands by Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala's will and instruction and shaitan ran away.

00:04:25.190 --> 00:04:28.190
They actually saw the Suraqah bin Malik go away.

00:04:28.190 --> 00:04:30.190
Abu Jahl tells him where are you going?

00:04:30.190 --> 00:04:32.190
He says no I am going and he began to run.

00:04:32.190 --> 00:04:35.190
They tried to get hold of him they couldn't he ran away.

00:04:35.190 --> 00:04:40.190
And this is mentioned in the Quran there is a verse Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says

00:04:40.190 --> 00:05:08.190
Don't be like those who came out of their homes in pride.

00:05:08.190 --> 00:05:14.190
Hurtiness arrogance in order to lead astray from the path of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:05:14.190 --> 00:05:17.190
Allah knows exactly what they were doing.

00:05:17.190 --> 00:05:22.190
So Allah is instructing not only the Muslim in at the time but all of us as well.

00:05:22.190 --> 00:05:30.190
We should abstain from pride and hurtiness and we should not be from amongst those who lead people astray from the path of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:05:30.190 --> 00:05:32.190
The very next verse Allah says

00:05:32.190 --> 00:05:51.190
And remember when shaitan beautified for them.

00:05:51.190 --> 00:05:58.190
When shaitan beautified for them and told them that I am going to be by your side.

00:05:58.190 --> 00:06:02.190
He beautified their deeds and he beautified their effort and their work.

00:06:02.190 --> 00:06:07.190
And he told them don't worry you will never lose I am right by your side.

00:06:07.190 --> 00:06:11.190
Then the verse continues Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says

00:06:19.190 --> 00:06:23.190
When the two armies finally clashed shaitan ran away.

00:06:23.190 --> 00:06:26.190
He turned his back and he was gone.

00:06:28.190 --> 00:06:38.190
And he told them I am free from you I am disassociating myself from you.

00:06:38.190 --> 00:06:50.190
I see that which you don't see which means the angels.

00:06:50.190 --> 00:06:56.190
I am witnessing I can see the angels I see that which you do not see and I fear Allah.

00:06:56.190 --> 00:07:03.190
Allah is indeed very severe when it comes to punishing.

00:07:03.190 --> 00:07:06.190
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us.

00:07:06.190 --> 00:07:09.190
From this we need to pause for a moment and look into our own lives.

00:07:09.190 --> 00:07:12.190
This is shaitan's plan.

00:07:12.190 --> 00:07:19.190
He helps a person to engage in wrong and makes him falsely feel that he is doing the right thing.

00:07:20.190 --> 00:07:27.190
Until when that person has got to a point shaitan then runs away and leaves him in the lurch.

00:07:27.190 --> 00:07:28.190
Let me give you an example.

00:07:28.190 --> 00:07:29.190
A gambler.

00:07:29.190 --> 00:07:33.190
A gambler will continue gambling thinking I am making more I am making more.

00:07:33.190 --> 00:07:38.190
Shaitan is by his side in the form of women, in the form of men, in the form of people giving money,

00:07:38.190 --> 00:07:40.190
in the form of borrowings and so on.

00:07:40.190 --> 00:07:43.190
Don't worry you are going to win you are going to win and he starts winning one two three.

00:07:43.190 --> 00:07:47.190
When the kill when the large amount is about to be lost shaitan is gone.

00:07:48.190 --> 00:07:50.190
When you lose it he is not there to help you.

00:07:50.190 --> 00:07:53.190
And then he is completely in disappearance.

00:07:53.190 --> 00:07:54.190
May Allah protect us.

00:07:54.190 --> 00:07:56.190
The same applies to adultery.

00:07:56.190 --> 00:07:58.190
A person is prodded everything seems to be nice.

00:07:58.190 --> 00:08:01.190
Everything is you know seemingly rosy.

00:08:01.190 --> 00:08:03.190
Shaitan goes and beautify everything.

00:08:03.190 --> 00:08:07.190
And thereafter when the act is committed and now people are caught red handed.

00:08:07.190 --> 00:08:08.190
Shaitan is gone.

00:08:08.190 --> 00:08:10.190
He doesn't help you out of your mess.

00:08:10.190 --> 00:08:11.190
Remember that.

00:08:11.190 --> 00:08:13.190
Shaitan's job is to get you into a mess.

00:08:13.190 --> 00:08:15.190
Once you are in it he is out.

00:08:15.190 --> 00:08:23.190
So a winner is the one who understands the plot of shaitan and does not allow himself or herself to fall into that plot in the first place.

00:08:23.190 --> 00:08:25.190
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us.

00:08:25.190 --> 00:08:27.190
This is the plot of shaitan in the battle of Badr.

00:08:27.190 --> 00:08:29.190
This is what he did to the mushrikeen.

00:08:29.190 --> 00:08:31.190
He made them feel they were doing the right thing.

00:08:31.190 --> 00:08:36.190
They were going out and he made them he was encouraging them to do this and to party and to do that.

00:08:36.190 --> 00:08:39.190
When it came to the war itself he ran away.

00:08:39.190 --> 00:08:41.190
And he says look I fear Allah.

00:08:41.190 --> 00:08:43.190
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala safeguard us.

00:08:43.190 --> 00:08:45.190
These are verses in the Quran.

00:08:45.190 --> 00:08:48.190
As we had said they had the duel.

00:08:48.190 --> 00:08:52.190
We want to quickly mention the names of the three from amongst the mushriks who had come forth.

00:08:52.190 --> 00:08:59.190
And the three from amongst the believers who had come forth in order to engage in the sword fight which usually commenced the war.

00:08:59.190 --> 00:09:00.190
What would happen?

00:09:00.190 --> 00:09:07.190
They would bring out the best of their warriors and these would engage in one on one fighting.

00:09:07.190 --> 00:09:11.190
And once that came to an end the armies would then clash.

00:09:11.190 --> 00:09:19.190
This was like a prelude and it was meant to infuriate the party who may have lost lives in that particular duel.

00:09:19.190 --> 00:09:22.190
So Hamza ibn Abdul Muttalib came out from the believers.

00:09:22.190 --> 00:09:30.190
Together with him Ali ibn Abi Talib radiallahu anhu came out and Ubaidah ibn Al-Harith radiallahu anhu came out.

00:09:30.190 --> 00:09:36.190
These three were out and on the other side the one who faced Hamza was Shaybah ibn Rabi'ah.

00:09:36.190 --> 00:09:41.190
And the one who faced Ubaidah ibn Al-Harith, his name was Utbah ibn Rabi'ah.

00:09:41.190 --> 00:09:49.190
And the one who faced Ali ibn Abi Talib radiallahu anhu, he was the son, Al-Waleed ibn Utbah, the son of Utbah ibn Rabi'ah.

00:09:49.190 --> 00:09:54.190
And Hamza radiallahu anhu struck his opponent, the opponent was executed.

00:09:54.190 --> 00:09:59.190
Ali radiallahu anhu in no time struck his opponent, the opponent was executed.

00:09:59.190 --> 00:10:07.190
But Ubaidah ibn Al-Harith radiallahu anhu, there was quite a bit of a fight that ensued between the two of them.

00:10:07.190 --> 00:10:13.190
And what happened, one struck the other, the other struck this one and Ubaidah had been quite injured.

00:10:13.190 --> 00:10:21.190
And at the same time this man was also Utbah, was injured until Hamza and Ali ibn Abi Talib radiallahu anhu,

00:10:21.190 --> 00:10:26.190
they came to the assistance of their man, of the Sahabi Ubaidah ibn Al-Harith and they helped him.

00:10:26.190 --> 00:10:31.190
And this is when all three of the mushriks were there slain.

00:10:31.190 --> 00:10:37.190
And this infuriated Abu Jahl and they became angry, their leaders were gone.

00:10:37.190 --> 00:10:43.190
They were so angry, they charged forth for the Muslimin who were given instruction not to move.

00:10:43.190 --> 00:10:45.190
They were standing in their rows.

00:10:45.190 --> 00:10:51.190
As they are charging, they were instructed by Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wasallam to fire.

00:10:52.190 --> 00:10:56.190
When they had come very close, when the enemy came very close.

00:10:56.190 --> 00:11:00.190
And so those with the arrows, released those arrows.

00:11:00.190 --> 00:11:02.190
Those with the spears, released the spears.

00:11:02.190 --> 00:11:06.190
And this resulted in many of those mushriks losing their lives.

00:11:06.190 --> 00:11:14.190
And thereafter, you find the, as they progressed further, they were instructed to fire again.

00:11:14.190 --> 00:11:18.190
And by this time the horsemen had already started coming.

00:11:18.190 --> 00:11:22.190
And a lot of the horses were attacked, they were harmed.

00:11:22.190 --> 00:11:28.190
And you know when a horse is hurt and when one drops, the others that are with it, they are confused.

00:11:28.190 --> 00:11:31.190
They want to turn back, some of them drop themselves as well.

00:11:31.190 --> 00:11:34.190
So a lot of chaos was caused.

00:11:34.190 --> 00:11:37.190
And thereafter, these people, the two armies had clashed.

00:11:37.190 --> 00:11:43.190
And this is when another instruction came for those with the swords to remove their swords and begin the fight.

00:11:43.190 --> 00:11:45.190
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us.

00:11:45.190 --> 00:11:47.190
These were brave people.

00:11:47.190 --> 00:11:54.190
We can even say that the mushriks of Mecca were brave enough to face the Muslims one on one.

00:11:54.190 --> 00:11:57.190
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us understanding.

00:11:57.190 --> 00:12:04.190
Allah says there are those who are coward, very cowardly, full of cowardice.

00:12:04.190 --> 00:12:06.190
Who will fight you from behind the walls.

00:12:06.190 --> 00:12:08.190
They won't come and attack you one on one.

00:12:08.190 --> 00:12:12.190
They will fight you from behind 45 walls and so on.

00:12:12.190 --> 00:12:14.190
But these were not the mushriks of Mecca.

00:12:14.190 --> 00:12:17.190
They had chosen to come and fight bravely.

00:12:17.190 --> 00:12:20.190
But at the same time, they started losing.

00:12:20.190 --> 00:12:28.190
And we want to make mention of a few of the people who had lost their lives from amongst the mushriks of Mecca.

00:12:28.190 --> 00:12:31.190
Firstly, their leader was Abu Jahl.

00:12:31.190 --> 00:12:33.190
Abu Jahl had people around him.

00:12:33.190 --> 00:12:36.190
And he was at a certain point where nobody could reach.

00:12:36.190 --> 00:12:39.190
The minute someone would go there, they would be tackled by someone.

00:12:39.190 --> 00:12:41.190
Because he was the leader of the army.

00:12:42.190 --> 00:12:45.190
This leader of the mushriks was far behind.

00:12:45.190 --> 00:12:46.190
He was being protected.

00:12:46.190 --> 00:12:52.190
So Abdur Rahman ibn Awf r.a. makes mention in a hadith which is also authentic.

00:12:52.190 --> 00:12:54.190
It is reported in Sahih al-Bukhari as well.

00:12:54.190 --> 00:12:58.190
There is a whole chapter, the chapter of the execution of Abu Jahl.

00:12:58.190 --> 00:13:01.190
And this is where some of the narrations are made mention of.

00:13:01.190 --> 00:13:08.190
And Abdur Rahman ibn Awf r.a. says there were two young boys from the Ansar.

00:13:09.190 --> 00:13:13.190
One was Mu'adh ibn Afra r.a.

00:13:13.190 --> 00:13:17.190
And the other one was Mu'adh ibn Amr ibn Al-Jamuh r.a.

00:13:17.190 --> 00:13:21.190
The two of them, young boys, came to me, he says.

00:13:21.190 --> 00:13:25.190
And they told me, uncle, literally that word, uncle.

00:13:25.190 --> 00:13:27.190
Who is Abu Jahl?

00:13:27.190 --> 00:13:31.190
So Abdur Rahman ibn Awf says, I looked at him and I said, what do you want with Abu Jahl?

00:13:31.190 --> 00:13:33.190
He is the leader of the Sahami here.

00:13:33.190 --> 00:13:34.190
What do you want with him?

00:13:34.190 --> 00:13:38.190
No, we've heard that he swears Rasulullah s.a.w.

00:13:38.190 --> 00:13:43.190
We've heard that he has caused much suffering to Rasulullah s.a.w.

00:13:43.190 --> 00:13:45.190
Today we want to sort him out.

00:13:45.190 --> 00:13:47.190
Subhanallah, young boys.

00:13:47.190 --> 00:13:55.190
Now had these people been older, they would not have been able to cross the lines and the ranks of the mushriks.

00:13:55.190 --> 00:13:59.190
Because their leader was heavily protected.

00:13:59.190 --> 00:14:02.190
But because they were young, they got away with it.

00:14:02.190 --> 00:14:06.190
What happened is Abdur Rahman ibn Awf says, after some time I saw Abu Jahl and I showed them.

00:14:06.190 --> 00:14:09.190
I say, there's the man. Don't worry, I'm not pointing at anyone here.

00:14:09.190 --> 00:14:11.190
We're pointing at the wall there, inshallah.

00:14:11.190 --> 00:14:15.190
So there he is and he shows them.

00:14:15.190 --> 00:14:17.190
They were so happy.

00:14:17.190 --> 00:14:21.190
He says, no sooner did I say this than they had already got to him.

00:14:21.190 --> 00:14:23.190
And what they had done?

00:14:23.190 --> 00:14:27.190
They got him off his little horse and they had started striking him.

00:14:27.190 --> 00:14:31.190
And the people around didn't even notice that these two were attacking.

00:14:31.190 --> 00:14:39.190
Besides, the son of Abu Jahl, Iqrimah ibn Abi Jahl, he struck one of them quite badly.

00:14:39.190 --> 00:14:46.190
In fact, he struck Mu'adh ibn Amr ibn Al-Jamuh to the degree that one narration says he lost part of his hand.

00:14:46.190 --> 00:14:54.190
But by this time, the youngster had already struck Abu Jahl who was on the ground and he was already almost complete, almost finished.

00:14:54.190 --> 00:14:57.190
He was just making a bit of noise this way, that way, breathing heavily.

00:14:57.190 --> 00:15:03.190
And he had already had bodily injuries that were quite severe.

00:15:03.190 --> 00:15:06.190
And in no time the other youngster comes.

00:15:06.190 --> 00:15:15.190
And when he came in Mu'adh ibn Afra, he had struck Abu Jahl and ensured that now there is no movement of this particular man.

00:15:15.190 --> 00:15:18.190
He was still breathing, but there was no movement.

00:15:18.190 --> 00:15:25.190
This was the leader of the Meccan army taken on by two little boys from the Ansar, subhanallah.

00:15:25.190 --> 00:15:32.190
And as for Mu'adh ibn Afra, in that particular battle he was martyred.

00:15:32.190 --> 00:15:38.190
He had fought and fought. Young boy, he fought so much and he was martyred by the will of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:15:38.190 --> 00:15:44.190
And as for the other Mu'adh, he had lived on quite long even after Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:15:44.190 --> 00:15:50.190
Abdullah ibn Mas'ud radiallahu anhu says after that battle, the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam asked a question.

00:15:50.190 --> 00:15:54.190
Where is this Abu Jahl? Who can go and see what has happened to him?

00:15:54.190 --> 00:16:00.190
And Abdullah ibn Mas'ud radiallahu anhu says when I went there, he was breathing his last, Abu Jahl was breathing his last.

00:16:00.190 --> 00:16:06.190
And there was a discussion between them. May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us from arrogance.

00:16:06.190 --> 00:16:14.190
When the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam had seen this man Abu Jahl executed, he declared the greatness of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:16:14.190 --> 00:16:16.190
That was one of the biggest enemies of Islam.

00:16:16.190 --> 00:16:21.190
So much so that one narration says that he was the Fir'aun of this Ummah.

00:16:21.190 --> 00:16:23.190
He was the Pharaoh of this Ummah.

00:16:23.190 --> 00:16:33.190
If you look at the Pharaoh of Musa a.s., when he had arrived at the point of his death, what did he say?

00:16:44.190 --> 00:16:51.190
Fir'aun says, the Pharaoh says, there is none worthy of worship besides the one whom Banu Israel are worshiping.

00:16:51.190 --> 00:16:56.190
The god of Musa, the god of Moses may peace be upon him. That's the one I believe in.

00:16:56.190 --> 00:16:58.190
But it was too late. Allah says,

00:17:07.190 --> 00:17:14.190
Is it now that you want to turn? And yet you had been so full of transgression in the past.

00:17:14.190 --> 00:17:20.190
Allahu Akbar, and you were from amongst the corrupt. It was too late. He had seen the angels of death.

00:17:20.190 --> 00:17:29.190
But he was better than Abu Jahl because Abu Jahl on his deathbed uttered words of blasphemy instead of turning to Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:17:29.190 --> 00:17:36.190
So imagine, when a person is now on his deathbed instead of uttering words of goodness, he utters bad words.

00:17:36.190 --> 00:17:41.190
So this was Abu Jahl and this is how he had actually been brought to an end.

00:17:41.190 --> 00:17:45.190
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us from all tyrants.

00:17:45.190 --> 00:17:54.190
The other man who was one of the leaders of Quraysh, we've heard already of Utbah ibn Rabi'ah and those who took part in the duel who had been executed.

00:17:54.190 --> 00:17:58.190
One of the people who was a leader was Umayyah ibn Khalaf.

00:17:58.190 --> 00:18:05.190
The same Abdulrahman ibn Awf says, I was a friend of Umayyah during our days in Makkah.

00:18:05.190 --> 00:18:11.190
I was a businessman. He was a businessman. And we had an understanding of protecting our interests.

00:18:12.190 --> 00:18:21.190
Until when I came to Madinah Munawwara, initially there was an understanding between us that you would protect my interests in Makkah and I will protect your interests in Madinah.

00:18:21.190 --> 00:18:27.190
So Abdulrahman ibn Awf felt that he needed to show this man that I am here to protect you.

00:18:27.190 --> 00:18:33.190
But at the same time, Abdulrahman ibn Awf was within the army of the Muslims.

00:18:33.190 --> 00:18:40.190
And what happened? Bilal ibn Rabi'ah when he saw Umayyah ibn Khalaf, it brought back all the memories.

00:18:40.190 --> 00:18:43.190
The memories of how he was tortured by this man.

00:18:43.190 --> 00:18:50.190
The man had taken him out into the heat of the desert and pulled him on the rocks of the hot Sahara desert.

00:18:50.190 --> 00:18:57.190
And at the same time, he had placed hot boulders over him on his chest and he was whipping him.

00:18:57.190 --> 00:19:01.190
He made him bleed and he continued saying go back and leave Muhammad.

00:19:01.190 --> 00:19:04.190
Stop saying one. Stop saying one.

00:19:04.190 --> 00:19:08.190
Ahadun Ahad was the word that Bilal ibn Rabi'ah was saying.

00:19:08.190 --> 00:19:14.190
For your information, during the wars, they normally had what is called a war cry.

00:19:14.190 --> 00:19:16.190
I'm sure you know the meaning of a war cry.

00:19:16.190 --> 00:19:19.190
So the Mushriks had their own statements they used to utter.

00:19:19.190 --> 00:19:24.190
The Muslims had powerful short words that they used to constantly repeat.

00:19:24.190 --> 00:19:31.190
It is reported in the narrations of the historians that the word repeated in the Battle of Badr was Ahadun Ahad.

00:19:31.190 --> 00:19:37.190
The same words that Bilal ibn Rabi'ah was saying when he was being harmed by Umayyah ibn Khalaf.

00:19:37.190 --> 00:19:42.190
And they heard Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam uttering other words.

00:19:42.190 --> 00:19:45.190
Do you know what he said? He kept on repeating

00:19:52.190 --> 00:19:53.190
It's a verse of the Quran.

00:19:53.190 --> 00:19:56.190
But he was repeating it sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:19:56.190 --> 00:20:00.190
It means this group of people will be overcome.

00:20:00.190 --> 00:20:02.190
They are going to lose and they're going to run away.

00:20:02.190 --> 00:20:04.190
They're going to flee. Subhanallah.

00:20:04.190 --> 00:20:05.190
They're going to run away.

00:20:05.190 --> 00:20:09.190
So he kept on repeating it sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:20:09.190 --> 00:20:13.190
And as for Bilal ibn Rabi'ah when he saw Umayyah ibn Khalaf,

00:20:13.190 --> 00:20:20.190
he told himself, I am not safe and I will not be saved if this man is saved today.

00:20:20.190 --> 00:20:24.190
So the Ansar, some of the people of Madina Munawarah who had heard the story,

00:20:24.190 --> 00:20:26.190
they knew what happened to Bilal ibn Rabi'ah.

00:20:26.190 --> 00:20:29.190
Some of them gathered with him and they started chasing.

00:20:29.190 --> 00:20:31.190
When they started chasing this man,

00:20:31.190 --> 00:20:35.190
Abdul Rahman ibn Awf went to him and tried to protect him

00:20:35.190 --> 00:20:38.190
in the sense that tried to give him a little bit of shelter and cover

00:20:38.190 --> 00:20:41.190
because this was the understanding between them.

00:20:41.190 --> 00:20:45.190
And Bilal ibn Rabi'ah radiallahu anhu,

00:20:45.190 --> 00:20:49.190
as this man was instructed to stop by Abdul Rahman ibn Awf,

00:20:49.190 --> 00:20:53.190
stop, don't worry, get off your horse, get off.

00:20:53.190 --> 00:20:58.190
And as he got off, Abdul Rahman ibn Awf covers him.

00:20:58.190 --> 00:21:03.190
And as he is covered, Bilal ibn Rabi'ah and the members of the Ansar

00:21:03.190 --> 00:21:06.190
strike him from beneath Abdul Rahman ibn Awf.

00:21:06.190 --> 00:21:10.190
They strike him and they get rid of him, subhanallah.

00:21:10.190 --> 00:21:14.190
They strike him, they injure him and he begins to bleed

00:21:14.190 --> 00:21:19.190
and at the same time Bilal ibn Rabi'ah was so thankful to Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:21:19.190 --> 00:21:22.190
for giving him a day of revenge and retaliation.

00:21:22.190 --> 00:21:24.190
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness.

00:21:24.190 --> 00:21:27.190
Remember, people might think that this sounds gruesome,

00:21:27.190 --> 00:21:28.190
it sounds awesome.

00:21:28.190 --> 00:21:31.190
These, it sounds gruesome.

00:21:31.190 --> 00:21:33.190
At the same time we need to understand

00:21:33.190 --> 00:21:35.190
these people were criminals.

00:21:35.190 --> 00:21:41.190
They were people who had perpetrated crimes against humanity.

00:21:41.190 --> 00:21:44.190
They had executed so many innocent people,

00:21:44.190 --> 00:21:48.190
stolen their wealth and they were actively engaged

00:21:48.190 --> 00:21:51.190
in military activity against the Muslims.

00:21:51.190 --> 00:21:53.190
And at the same time if you look at them,

00:21:53.190 --> 00:21:55.190
it was them who wanted to fight in Badr,

00:21:56.190 --> 00:21:57.190
not the Muslims.

00:21:57.190 --> 00:21:59.190
The Muslims had come out for something else.

00:21:59.190 --> 00:22:01.190
Abu Jahl was the one who insisted

00:22:01.190 --> 00:22:05.190
because shaitan made him feel that today you're going to win.

00:22:05.190 --> 00:22:09.190
He is the one who insisted we want to fight these Muslims no matter what.

00:22:09.190 --> 00:22:13.190
So this was something Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says in the Quran.

00:22:13.190 --> 00:22:32.190
...

00:22:32.190 --> 00:22:33.190
Powerful verses of the Quran.

00:22:33.190 --> 00:22:36.190
Allah says if you, the two armies,

00:22:36.190 --> 00:22:38.190
had made an appointed time to fight,

00:22:38.190 --> 00:22:40.190
perhaps you wouldn't have clashed,

00:22:40.190 --> 00:22:41.190
you wouldn't have met.

00:22:41.190 --> 00:22:43.190
This was planned by Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:22:43.190 --> 00:22:46.190
Allah says Allah intended for that

00:22:46.190 --> 00:22:50.190
which was made to come to pass, to come to pass.

00:22:50.190 --> 00:22:52.190
So this was Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala's plan.

00:22:52.190 --> 00:22:57.190
He says to destroy those who were destroyed upon evidence.

00:22:57.190 --> 00:22:59.190
They knew what was right and wrong, they were destroyed.

00:22:59.190 --> 00:23:02.190
And to allow those who won and who lived,

00:23:02.190 --> 00:23:05.190
to live with evidence upon evidence,

00:23:05.190 --> 00:23:07.190
they knew that we are on the right path.

00:23:07.190 --> 00:23:09.190
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us

00:23:09.190 --> 00:23:11.190
the ability to understand his plan

00:23:11.190 --> 00:23:13.190
and to follow it at all times

00:23:13.190 --> 00:23:15.190
and not to follow the plan of shaitan.

00:23:15.190 --> 00:23:18.190
When the war was over,

00:23:18.190 --> 00:23:22.190
70 of the disbelievers had lost their life, 70.

00:23:22.190 --> 00:23:26.190
And they were approximately between 900 and a thousand

00:23:26.190 --> 00:23:28.190
when they had now arrived in Badr.

00:23:28.190 --> 00:23:29.190
We explained when they left Makkah,

00:23:29.190 --> 00:23:31.190
they were a little bit more in number.

00:23:31.190 --> 00:23:32.190
But when they got to Badr,

00:23:32.190 --> 00:23:34.190
they were less because of the letter

00:23:34.190 --> 00:23:36.190
that Abu Sufyan had written to say you may now go back.

00:23:36.190 --> 00:23:38.190
And some of the clans went back

00:23:38.190 --> 00:23:40.190
and some of the people went back.

00:23:40.190 --> 00:23:43.190
So they had lost 70 of their lives

00:23:43.190 --> 00:23:48.190
and 70 of their men were taken prisoner of war.

00:23:48.190 --> 00:23:50.190
They were taken captive.

00:23:50.190 --> 00:23:52.190
And from amongst the believers,

00:23:52.190 --> 00:23:54.190
14 men were martyred, subhanAllah.

00:23:54.190 --> 00:23:56.190
Look at the figures.

00:23:56.190 --> 00:23:58.190
These were only 313,

00:23:58.190 --> 00:24:01.190
they're going back with 299, subhanAllah.

00:24:01.190 --> 00:24:05.190
And those, the rest of them fled, they ran away.

00:24:05.190 --> 00:24:08.190
And they had a silly system.

00:24:08.190 --> 00:24:11.190
Their system was when we go out for war,

00:24:11.190 --> 00:24:14.190
we take with us a lot of our jewellery

00:24:14.190 --> 00:24:15.190
and a lot of our wealth

00:24:15.190 --> 00:24:17.190
and a lot of this and a lot of that.

00:24:17.190 --> 00:24:19.190
So they had come with a lot of their wealth and jewellery

00:24:19.190 --> 00:24:22.190
and a lot of their belongings and merchandise and so on.

00:24:22.190 --> 00:24:23.190
And do you know what?

00:24:23.190 --> 00:24:24.190
They ran away.

00:24:24.190 --> 00:24:27.190
When they ran away and they left everything on that battlefield,

00:24:27.190 --> 00:24:30.190
subhanAllah, the Muslims,

00:24:30.190 --> 00:24:32.190
this was their ghanima.

00:24:32.190 --> 00:24:34.190
Ghanima meaning it was the spoils of war.

00:24:34.190 --> 00:24:36.190
One might call it booty.

00:24:36.190 --> 00:24:39.190
It was that which was left behind by the kuffar as they flee,

00:24:39.190 --> 00:24:41.190
as they fled.

00:24:41.190 --> 00:24:45.190
And this is why the Muslims were instructed,

00:24:45.190 --> 00:24:47.190
they began to gather the items

00:24:47.190 --> 00:24:50.190
that were left behind by the mushrikeen.

00:24:50.190 --> 00:24:54.190
So they had lost 14 lives, the Muslims.

00:24:54.190 --> 00:24:55.190
14 of them were martyred,

00:24:55.190 --> 00:24:56.190
6 from amongst the muhajireen

00:24:56.190 --> 00:24:58.190
and 8 from amongst the ansar.

00:24:58.190 --> 00:25:02.190
The Prophet ﷺ immediately sent 2 men to Madinah Munawwara

00:25:03.190 --> 00:25:05.190
to inform them of what happened.

00:25:05.190 --> 00:25:08.190
And this was the good news that got to Madinah Munawwara,

00:25:08.190 --> 00:25:10.190
but it was bad news for some people.

00:25:10.190 --> 00:25:11.190
We'll explain who.

00:25:11.190 --> 00:25:13.190
Who were the 2 who were sent?

00:25:13.190 --> 00:25:15.190
Abdullah ibn Rawaha r.a.

00:25:15.190 --> 00:25:16.190
and Zayd ibn Haritha.

00:25:16.190 --> 00:25:19.190
They were sent back to Madinah Munawwara with the news.

00:25:19.190 --> 00:25:22.190
So when the news came to got to Madinah Munawwara,

00:25:22.190 --> 00:25:25.190
the Muslims were so happy, so excited.

00:25:25.190 --> 00:25:30.190
They knew, they said Allah has fulfilled His promise to us

00:25:30.190 --> 00:25:32.190
and Allah has granted us victory.

00:25:32.190 --> 00:25:35.190
And they could not believe that the same people

00:25:35.190 --> 00:25:37.190
who had persecuted them

00:25:37.190 --> 00:25:40.190
and executed or murdered some of them

00:25:40.190 --> 00:25:42.190
were now themselves executed.

00:25:42.190 --> 00:25:45.190
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us victory upon victory.

00:25:45.190 --> 00:25:46.190
What happened?

00:25:46.190 --> 00:25:49.190
They were very happy, delighted.

00:25:49.190 --> 00:25:52.190
At the same time, the people of the book,

00:25:52.190 --> 00:25:54.190
the people of Banu Qainuqa,

00:25:54.190 --> 00:25:56.190
Banu An-Nadheer, Banu Quraidha,

00:25:56.190 --> 00:25:57.190
they were upset.

00:25:58.190 --> 00:26:00.190
And the hypocrites, Abdullah ibn Ubayy ibn Salul,

00:26:00.190 --> 00:26:02.190
they were upset.

00:26:02.190 --> 00:26:03.190
Why were they angry?

00:26:03.190 --> 00:26:06.190
They were not expecting the Muslims to win.

00:26:06.190 --> 00:26:09.190
They were hoping that the messenger be executed,

00:26:09.190 --> 00:26:12.190
everyone be executed, Quraish can win

00:26:12.190 --> 00:26:16.190
and we can now be the leaders once again of Madinah Munawwara.

00:26:16.190 --> 00:26:17.190
So they were very upset.

00:26:17.190 --> 00:26:21.190
They were so angry that they started planning and plotting

00:26:21.190 --> 00:26:23.190
and they became very loud mouth

00:26:23.190 --> 00:26:25.190
and said you people went out only because

00:26:25.190 --> 00:26:27.190
you wanted to get the spoils and you wanted this

00:26:27.190 --> 00:26:28.190
and you were greedy and so on,

00:26:28.190 --> 00:26:31.190
statements that were flying around under cover.

00:26:31.190 --> 00:26:35.190
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala exposes these people

00:26:35.190 --> 00:26:39.190
and Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam knew them

00:26:39.190 --> 00:26:42.190
and what had happened as the messengers came back

00:26:42.190 --> 00:26:45.190
when the Muslims saw the captives,

00:26:45.190 --> 00:26:48.190
this is when they knew something has happened here.

00:26:48.190 --> 00:26:52.190
Imagine the power that Islam and the Muslims had achieved

00:26:52.190 --> 00:26:54.190
by conquering the superpower of the time

00:26:54.190 --> 00:26:57.190
who was Quraish with a meager force, small force

00:26:57.190 --> 00:27:00.190
and this is mentioned in all the books of Seerah.

00:27:00.190 --> 00:27:02.190
They returned to Al-Madinah al-Munawwara

00:27:02.190 --> 00:27:05.190
with 70 of their men, minus two.

00:27:05.190 --> 00:27:06.190
Why minus two?

00:27:06.190 --> 00:27:08.190
Meaning 70 of the captives.

00:27:08.190 --> 00:27:13.190
Two of them, they were court-martialed on the way back

00:27:13.190 --> 00:27:15.190
by the messenger sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:27:15.190 --> 00:27:17.190
they were found to be criminals

00:27:17.190 --> 00:27:20.190
who had perpetrated crimes against humanity

00:27:20.190 --> 00:27:22.190
and they were executed there and then.

00:27:22.190 --> 00:27:23.190
Who were they?

00:27:23.190 --> 00:27:26.190
Uqbah ibn Abi Mu'ayt, one of them.

00:27:26.190 --> 00:27:28.190
May Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam safeguard us

00:27:28.190 --> 00:27:30.190
and may He grant us goodness.

00:27:30.190 --> 00:27:33.190
And Annadr ibn al-Harith, he was the other one.

00:27:33.190 --> 00:27:36.190
These were the ones who had harassed and hassled

00:27:36.190 --> 00:27:39.190
not only the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam personally,

00:27:39.190 --> 00:27:41.190
they were guilty of war crimes

00:27:41.190 --> 00:27:44.190
and they were the ones who had persecuted

00:27:44.190 --> 00:27:47.190
and executed people in Makkah al-Mukarramah.

00:27:47.190 --> 00:27:48.190
So they were court-martialed.

00:27:48.190 --> 00:27:51.190
Court-martialed meaning they were not just killed for no reason.

00:27:51.190 --> 00:27:53.190
They were found guilty of crimes against humanity

00:27:53.190 --> 00:27:54.190
and they were executed.

00:27:54.190 --> 00:27:55.190
These were the two.

00:27:55.190 --> 00:27:56.190
The rest of them came back

00:27:56.190 --> 00:28:00.190
and the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam made an announcement.

00:28:00.190 --> 00:28:02.190
Be careful how you treat the prisoners of war.

00:28:02.190 --> 00:28:04.190
They are human beings just like you.

00:28:04.190 --> 00:28:06.190
You should feed them, you should clothe them,

00:28:06.190 --> 00:28:07.190
you should not harm them,

00:28:07.190 --> 00:28:09.190
you should provide for them shelter,

00:28:09.190 --> 00:28:12.190
you should ensure that you treat them in a humane way.

00:28:12.190 --> 00:28:15.190
All this is recorded in the books not only of hadith

00:28:15.190 --> 00:28:16.190
but the books of history.

00:28:16.190 --> 00:28:19.190
These are the words of Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:28:19.190 --> 00:28:23.190
the first nation that ever granted rights to prisoners of war

00:28:23.190 --> 00:28:25.190
was the nation of the Muslims.

00:28:25.190 --> 00:28:28.190
The Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam was the first man

00:28:28.190 --> 00:28:31.190
who treated the prisoners of war as human beings

00:28:31.190 --> 00:28:34.190
who were granted two meals a day.

00:28:34.190 --> 00:28:35.190
Subhanallah.

00:28:35.190 --> 00:28:38.190
And at that time they barely ate a meal a day.

00:28:38.190 --> 00:28:39.190
Subhanallah.

00:28:39.190 --> 00:28:41.190
They were respected.

00:28:41.190 --> 00:28:44.190
In fact there is a certain one of them

00:28:44.190 --> 00:28:48.190
who was very bad mouth against the Muslims

00:28:48.190 --> 00:28:50.190
when he was in Makkah al-Mukarramah.

00:28:50.190 --> 00:28:53.190
He was from amongst the prisoners of war.

00:28:53.190 --> 00:28:55.190
His name was Suhail ibn Amr.

00:28:55.190 --> 00:28:56.190
He was so eloquent,

00:28:56.190 --> 00:28:59.190
he used to give lectures against the Muslims.

00:28:59.190 --> 00:29:02.190
So Umar ibn Al-Khattab radiallahu anhu saw him

00:29:02.190 --> 00:29:04.190
and said, O Messenger sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:29:04.190 --> 00:29:07.190
let me fist this man one and break all his teeth.

00:29:07.190 --> 00:29:09.190
He won't be able to talk after today.

00:29:09.190 --> 00:29:11.190
The Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam says,

00:29:11.190 --> 00:29:13.190
I have been sent as a mercy.

00:29:13.190 --> 00:29:14.190
These are prisoners of war.

00:29:14.190 --> 00:29:16.190
We have never been taught to harm them

00:29:16.190 --> 00:29:19.190
and we are not taught to remove their organs or even their teeth.

00:29:19.190 --> 00:29:21.190
May Allah protect us.

00:29:21.190 --> 00:29:22.190
Not to be harmed.

00:29:22.190 --> 00:29:23.190
This is a lesson.

00:29:23.190 --> 00:29:28.190
Islam has taught us justice even during war.

00:29:28.190 --> 00:29:31.190
It's the only religion that has such upright teachings

00:29:31.190 --> 00:29:34.190
that even during war we are just.

00:29:34.190 --> 00:29:36.190
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us.

00:29:36.190 --> 00:29:37.190
This was the war.

00:29:37.190 --> 00:29:40.190
The first major battle people were learning.

00:29:40.190 --> 00:29:42.190
The mushriks were learning

00:29:42.190 --> 00:29:44.190
because they were prisoners of war watching what was going on.

00:29:44.190 --> 00:29:45.190
None of them was maltreated.

00:29:45.190 --> 00:29:48.190
And they knew why two of their people were executed.

00:29:48.190 --> 00:29:50.190
They knew that they deserved that.

00:29:50.190 --> 00:29:53.190
And the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam then,

00:29:53.190 --> 00:29:57.190
subhanallah, after having instructed his companions,

00:29:57.190 --> 00:30:00.190
meaning his companions regarding these captives,

00:30:00.190 --> 00:30:02.190
he then asks them,

00:30:02.190 --> 00:30:04.190
what should we do with these people?

00:30:04.190 --> 00:30:05.190
We have options.

00:30:05.190 --> 00:30:09.190
One of the options is we can execute.

00:30:09.190 --> 00:30:11.190
Court marshal them one after the other

00:30:11.190 --> 00:30:13.190
and see who is guilty and see what we want to do.

00:30:13.190 --> 00:30:15.190
Execute them one after the other.

00:30:15.190 --> 00:30:19.190
And the other is perhaps we can accept a ransom from them,

00:30:19.190 --> 00:30:21.190
meaning making them pay a fine

00:30:21.190 --> 00:30:23.190
for fighting against the Muslims.

00:30:23.190 --> 00:30:24.190
That's basically what it was.

00:30:24.190 --> 00:30:26.190
People call it different terms.

00:30:26.190 --> 00:30:28.190
We can choose to call it what we like.

00:30:28.190 --> 00:30:31.190
What is meant by it is what is more important.

00:30:31.190 --> 00:30:33.190
So what is the meaning of it is

00:30:33.190 --> 00:30:35.190
we will make them pay a fine

00:30:35.190 --> 00:30:37.190
for having taken part in the war against us.

00:30:37.190 --> 00:30:39.190
And then when they have paid that amount,

00:30:39.190 --> 00:30:40.190
we can free them.

00:30:41.190 --> 00:30:43.190
This was known as Al-Fida.

00:30:43.190 --> 00:30:47.190
They were supposed to pay an amount.

00:30:47.190 --> 00:30:50.190
So Umar ibn Al-Khattab radiallahu anhu says,

00:30:50.190 --> 00:30:52.190
Ya Rasulallah, sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:30:52.190 --> 00:30:53.190
these are the enemies.

00:30:53.190 --> 00:30:55.190
They're going to go back, regroup,

00:30:55.190 --> 00:30:57.190
come back and fight us again.

00:30:57.190 --> 00:30:59.190
What's the point of releasing them?

00:30:59.190 --> 00:31:03.190
We'd rather do what the other option was.

00:31:03.190 --> 00:31:05.190
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us.

00:31:05.190 --> 00:31:08.190
Umar ibn Al-Khattab was quite a tough man.

00:31:08.190 --> 00:31:12.190
Sa'd ibn Mu'adh radiallahu anhu shared his opinion.

00:31:12.190 --> 00:31:15.190
He says, oh, you know, I wished that we didn't have

00:31:15.190 --> 00:31:18.190
people who were captive that we would take back.

00:31:18.190 --> 00:31:23.190
Sa'd ibn Mu'adh was from the Ous in Madinah Munawwarah.

00:31:23.190 --> 00:31:27.190
And as for Abu Bakr and the majority of the Sahaba,

00:31:27.190 --> 00:31:28.190
they told Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:31:28.190 --> 00:31:31.190
O messenger, sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:31:31.190 --> 00:31:34.190
these people, they seem to be remorseful.

00:31:34.190 --> 00:31:36.190
You can accept from them some form of an amount

00:31:36.190 --> 00:31:38.190
or the fine and thereafter you can release them

00:31:38.190 --> 00:31:41.190
one after the other as you feel correct.

00:31:41.190 --> 00:31:44.190
So the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam then agreed

00:31:44.190 --> 00:31:46.190
regarding the rest of the army,

00:31:46.190 --> 00:31:48.190
besides the two who were already executed

00:31:48.190 --> 00:31:51.190
according to the statement of Umar ibn Al-Khattab radiallahu anhu,

00:31:51.190 --> 00:31:53.190
the rest of the army, he agreed,

00:31:53.190 --> 00:31:56.190
we will put a tag for every single one of them

00:31:56.190 --> 00:31:58.190
depending on their financial condition

00:31:58.190 --> 00:32:03.190
and thereafter we will release them one after the other.

00:32:03.190 --> 00:32:05.190
So those who were very poor,

00:32:05.190 --> 00:32:07.190
they were instructed to do something else.

00:32:07.190 --> 00:32:09.190
Those who were extremely wealthy,

00:32:09.190 --> 00:32:11.190
they paid the maximum amount.

00:32:11.190 --> 00:32:14.190
So it's not like people who were more wealthy

00:32:14.190 --> 00:32:15.190
had to pay more.

00:32:15.190 --> 00:32:17.190
No, there was a maximum amount,

00:32:17.190 --> 00:32:19.190
then they were literally discounts for some people,

00:32:19.190 --> 00:32:22.190
which means some people who were kind to the Muslimin

00:32:22.190 --> 00:32:24.190
in the past, who had looked after,

00:32:24.190 --> 00:32:27.190
who had had a few good habits and qualities in the past,

00:32:27.190 --> 00:32:29.190
they were treated slightly more leniently

00:32:29.190 --> 00:32:32.190
because of the goodness of the past.

00:32:32.190 --> 00:32:33.190
So from amongst these,

00:32:33.190 --> 00:32:36.190
we'd like to make mention of some of these people.

00:32:36.190 --> 00:32:41.190
Firstly, the story of Umar ibn Abi Sufyan,

00:32:41.190 --> 00:32:45.190
Abu Sufyan's son was one of those who was caught

00:32:45.190 --> 00:32:49.190
and Abu Sufyan was told that they are asking for X amount

00:32:49.190 --> 00:32:50.190
and they will free him.

00:32:50.190 --> 00:32:55.190
He says, I will never ever allow my son and my wealth

00:32:55.190 --> 00:32:57.190
to go to the Muslims, not both of them.

00:32:57.190 --> 00:32:59.190
We will sort this out in another way.

00:32:59.190 --> 00:33:02.190
And when one of the Sahaba radiallahu anhu

00:33:02.190 --> 00:33:05.190
whose name was Sa'd ibn al-Nu'man al-Ansari,

00:33:05.190 --> 00:33:07.190
when he had gone for Umrah,

00:33:07.190 --> 00:33:09.190
he was quietly in Makkah al-Mukarramah,

00:33:09.190 --> 00:33:11.190
Abu Sufyan got hold of him

00:33:11.190 --> 00:33:13.190
and sent a message to Madinah Munawwarah,

00:33:13.190 --> 00:33:15.190
release my son and I release this man.

00:33:15.190 --> 00:33:18.190
Look at him, intelligent man.

00:33:18.190 --> 00:33:21.190
We said he was extremely intelligent, Abu Sufyan.

00:33:21.190 --> 00:33:24.190
So the Prophet salallahu alayhi wasallam heard the news

00:33:24.190 --> 00:33:27.190
and he released this man because obviously

00:33:27.190 --> 00:33:29.190
it was worth the Muslim being released

00:33:29.190 --> 00:33:31.190
from captivity there in Makkah al-Mukarramah

00:33:31.190 --> 00:33:34.190
and this is how the son of Abu Sufyan was released.

00:33:34.190 --> 00:33:39.190
Then we have a very, very touching story.

00:33:39.190 --> 00:33:42.190
Abu al-Aas ibn al-Rabiyah,

00:33:42.190 --> 00:33:44.190
he was the husband of the daughter

00:33:44.190 --> 00:33:46.190
of the Prophet salallahu alayhi wasallam

00:33:46.190 --> 00:33:48.190
whose name was Zainab.

00:33:48.190 --> 00:33:52.190
So he was the son-in-law of Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasallam.

00:33:52.190 --> 00:33:55.190
And in Makkah, he did not accept Islam.

00:33:55.190 --> 00:33:58.190
His daughter was a Muslim, she had accepted Islam.

00:33:58.190 --> 00:34:00.190
She wanted to come out for Hijra,

00:34:00.190 --> 00:34:01.190
he blocked her.

00:34:01.190 --> 00:34:02.190
He said you're not going anywhere.

00:34:02.190 --> 00:34:05.190
So she was one of those who could not make the Hijra.

00:34:05.190 --> 00:34:07.190
She was stuck in Makkah.

00:34:07.190 --> 00:34:09.190
Her husband was a very good man

00:34:09.190 --> 00:34:11.190
because Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasallam says

00:34:11.190 --> 00:34:13.190
that this al-Aas ibn al-Rabiyah,

00:34:13.190 --> 00:34:15.190
we've never had a problem with him.

00:34:15.190 --> 00:34:17.190
He has honored my daughter,

00:34:17.190 --> 00:34:18.190
he's looked after her so well

00:34:18.190 --> 00:34:20.190
and he is not a bad man

00:34:20.190 --> 00:34:22.190
besides the fact that he's a mushrik.

00:34:22.190 --> 00:34:24.190
He has not accepted Islam.

00:34:24.190 --> 00:34:26.190
But now the difficulty was

00:34:26.190 --> 00:34:29.190
he came with the army in order to fight.

00:34:29.190 --> 00:34:31.190
There were some people who came to fight

00:34:31.190 --> 00:34:33.190
because they couldn't remain behind in Makkah,

00:34:33.190 --> 00:34:35.190
they had to show face.

00:34:35.190 --> 00:34:37.190
So Abu al-Aas ibn al-Rabiyah,

00:34:37.190 --> 00:34:40.190
he came to Badr, to Madinah Munawwarah,

00:34:40.190 --> 00:34:42.190
close to Madinah, Badr,

00:34:42.190 --> 00:34:43.190
and he came to fight.

00:34:43.190 --> 00:34:45.190
Now that he was captured,

00:34:45.190 --> 00:34:49.190
he was told you need to pay this amount.

00:34:49.190 --> 00:34:51.190
So he sends message to his family

00:34:51.190 --> 00:34:53.190
in Makkah al-Mukarrama,

00:34:53.190 --> 00:34:56.190
made up of the daughter of Rasulullah salallahu alayhi wasallam.

00:34:56.190 --> 00:34:59.190
And when the amount came,

00:34:59.190 --> 00:35:01.190
he was instructed to pay a certain amount.

00:35:01.190 --> 00:35:02.190
When it came,

00:35:02.190 --> 00:35:04.190
it came in the form of a necklace,

00:35:04.190 --> 00:35:07.190
a gold necklace.

00:35:07.190 --> 00:35:09.190
And this gold necklace

00:35:09.190 --> 00:35:11.190
was the same necklace

00:35:11.190 --> 00:35:14.190
that the wife of Rasulullah salallahu alayhi wasallam

00:35:14.190 --> 00:35:16.190
who was the mother of Zainab,

00:35:16.190 --> 00:35:19.190
binti Rasulullah salallahu alayhi wasallam,

00:35:19.190 --> 00:35:20.190
Khadija binti Khawaylin,

00:35:20.190 --> 00:35:23.190
had given her daughter the day she got married.

00:35:23.190 --> 00:35:25.190
This is a gift for you, my daughter,

00:35:25.190 --> 00:35:27.190
if you're getting married to this al-Aas ibn al-Rabi'a,

00:35:27.190 --> 00:35:29.190
take this and carry on.

00:35:29.190 --> 00:35:33.190
So when the Prophet salallahu alayhi wasallam

00:35:33.190 --> 00:35:36.190
saw that the ransom that has come

00:35:36.190 --> 00:35:38.190
for this al-Aas ibn al-Rabi'a,

00:35:38.190 --> 00:35:40.190
who is my son-in-law,

00:35:40.190 --> 00:35:43.190
is made up of a gold chain

00:35:43.190 --> 00:35:46.190
which was given to my daughter by my wife,

00:35:46.190 --> 00:35:48.190
رضي الله عنهم جميعاً

00:35:48.190 --> 00:35:50.190
Allah be pleased with all of them.

00:35:50.190 --> 00:35:52.190
Immediately he told his companions,

00:35:53.190 --> 00:35:55.190
I want to ask you,

00:35:55.190 --> 00:36:01.190
if you feel fit to return this piece of jewelry to Zainab,

00:36:01.190 --> 00:36:03.190
then you can do so.

00:36:03.190 --> 00:36:05.190
The reason is she is a Muslima

00:36:05.190 --> 00:36:08.190
and she is paying from her own wealth.

00:36:08.190 --> 00:36:10.190
And obviously this is something

00:36:10.190 --> 00:36:12.190
that was given as a gift to her

00:36:12.190 --> 00:36:15.190
by one of the women who was the closest

00:36:15.190 --> 00:36:18.190
to Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasallam's heart.

00:36:18.190 --> 00:36:20.190
And still he did not just make a decision,

00:36:20.190 --> 00:36:21.190
he is telling the Sahaba,

00:36:21.190 --> 00:36:24.190
if you feel that this is correct, we can do this.

00:36:24.190 --> 00:36:27.190
So they agreed that yes it is correct,

00:36:27.190 --> 00:36:29.190
Subhanallah, Subhanallah.

00:36:29.190 --> 00:36:32.190
And they returned Abu al-Aas

00:36:32.190 --> 00:36:35.190
with the piece of jewelry on one condition.

00:36:35.190 --> 00:36:37.190
What was the condition?

00:36:37.190 --> 00:36:40.190
The condition was, you go to Makkah

00:36:40.190 --> 00:36:42.190
and you allow my daughter to make

00:36:42.190 --> 00:36:43.190
the Hijra to Madinah Munawwara,

00:36:43.190 --> 00:36:45.190
don't block her anymore.

00:36:45.190 --> 00:36:47.190
So he agreed when he went there,

00:36:47.190 --> 00:36:48.190
the Prophet salallahu alayhi wasallam

00:36:48.190 --> 00:36:50.190
had sent some people to collect his daughter

00:36:50.190 --> 00:36:53.190
Zainab binti Rasulullah salallahu alayhi wasallam

00:36:53.190 --> 00:36:56.190
and she had then come to Madinah Munawwara.

00:36:56.190 --> 00:36:58.190
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us

00:36:58.190 --> 00:37:00.190
an understanding that al-Aas ibn al-Rabi'a,

00:37:00.190 --> 00:37:02.190
he did not accept Islam immediately,

00:37:02.190 --> 00:37:04.190
but when he accepted Islam

00:37:04.190 --> 00:37:07.190
just before the victory of Makkah,

00:37:07.190 --> 00:37:08.190
the Prophet salallahu alayhi wasallam

00:37:08.190 --> 00:37:11.190
returned his daughter to al-Aas ibn al-Rabi'a

00:37:11.190 --> 00:37:13.190
without any new nikah.

00:37:13.190 --> 00:37:15.190
He said, this is still your wife

00:37:15.190 --> 00:37:16.190
and you can take her back.

00:37:16.190 --> 00:37:18.190
This was the instruction of Rasulullah

00:37:18.190 --> 00:37:20.190
salallahu alayhi wasallam,

00:37:20.190 --> 00:37:22.190
although it happened many years later,

00:37:22.190 --> 00:37:24.190
but he returned the wife to the husband.

00:37:24.190 --> 00:37:27.190
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness.

00:37:27.190 --> 00:37:29.190
This was the honor of the man

00:37:29.190 --> 00:37:31.190
who was kind to the family members

00:37:31.190 --> 00:37:34.190
of Rasulullah salallahu alayhi wasallam.

00:37:34.190 --> 00:37:36.190
Another man who was from amongst the captives

00:37:36.190 --> 00:37:38.190
was al-Walid ibn al-Walid,

00:37:38.190 --> 00:37:40.190
the brother of Khalid ibn al-Walid.

00:37:40.190 --> 00:37:42.190
His name was al-Walid ibn al-Walid.

00:37:42.190 --> 00:37:44.190
They sent message to Khalid,

00:37:44.190 --> 00:37:46.190
you need to pay the amount.

00:37:46.190 --> 00:37:47.190
Khalid paid the amount,

00:37:47.190 --> 00:37:49.190
al-Walid ibn al-Walid went back to Makkah,

00:37:49.190 --> 00:37:51.190
accepted Islam there,

00:37:51.190 --> 00:37:53.190
and after some time came to Madinah Munawwar.

00:37:53.190 --> 00:37:55.190
They asked him, why did you accept Islam

00:37:55.190 --> 00:37:56.190
after you came back?

00:37:56.190 --> 00:37:58.190
You should have just told him

00:37:58.190 --> 00:37:59.190
you want to accept Islam.

00:37:59.190 --> 00:38:01.190
His response was,

00:38:01.190 --> 00:38:03.190
I did not want them to think

00:38:03.190 --> 00:38:04.190
that I am entering Islam

00:38:04.190 --> 00:38:07.190
because I am frightened and I am scared.

00:38:07.190 --> 00:38:10.190
Sometimes people might think

00:38:10.190 --> 00:38:11.190
that this man entered Islam

00:38:11.190 --> 00:38:13.190
because he was frightened, he was scared.

00:38:13.190 --> 00:38:16.190
So he says, I wanted to sort the matter out,

00:38:16.190 --> 00:38:18.190
but Islam is the religion.

00:38:18.190 --> 00:38:20.190
He saw how the captives were being treated,

00:38:20.190 --> 00:38:21.190
what happened in war,

00:38:21.190 --> 00:38:23.190
the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم's justice,

00:38:23.190 --> 00:38:26.190
how the captives were honored

00:38:26.190 --> 00:38:28.190
by those who had captured them.

00:38:28.190 --> 00:38:30.190
Even though they themselves

00:38:30.190 --> 00:38:31.190
may not have had enough,

00:38:31.190 --> 00:38:34.190
they still gave a lot to these people.

00:38:34.190 --> 00:38:36.190
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness.

00:38:36.190 --> 00:38:38.190
Another man who was amongst those

00:38:38.190 --> 00:38:41.190
who was caught on that day as a prisoner of war

00:38:41.190 --> 00:38:44.190
was Wahab ibn Umayr al-Jumahi.

00:38:44.190 --> 00:38:46.190
His father was a friend of Safwan ibn Umayyah,

00:38:46.190 --> 00:38:48.190
Amr al-Jumahi.

00:38:48.190 --> 00:38:50.190
And Safwan ibn Umayyah,

00:38:50.190 --> 00:38:51.190
what he did,

00:38:51.190 --> 00:38:54.190
he was speaking to this man Umayyah al-Jumahi

00:38:54.190 --> 00:38:56.190
and he says to him, Umayyah al-Jumahi,

00:38:56.190 --> 00:38:58.190
he says, you know what?

00:38:58.190 --> 00:38:59.190
Umayyah says,

00:38:59.190 --> 00:39:01.190
if I didn't have so many children

00:39:01.190 --> 00:39:03.190
and if I didn't have so many people

00:39:03.190 --> 00:39:04.190
to look after and this and that,

00:39:04.190 --> 00:39:05.190
I would have gone

00:39:05.190 --> 00:39:07.190
and I would have executed Muhammad myself

00:39:07.190 --> 00:39:09.190
and I would have taken my child and come back.

00:39:09.190 --> 00:39:11.190
So Safwan ibn Umayyah told him,

00:39:11.190 --> 00:39:13.190
they were in the house, just the two of them.

00:39:13.190 --> 00:39:15.190
He says, look, I'll look after your family,

00:39:15.190 --> 00:39:16.190
I'll pay all your debts,

00:39:16.190 --> 00:39:18.190
I'll look after all your affairs,

00:39:18.190 --> 00:39:20.190
you go and do what you said you want to do.

00:39:20.190 --> 00:39:22.190
The man said, okay.

00:39:22.190 --> 00:39:24.190
And he took his sword and he went to Madinah.

00:39:24.190 --> 00:39:27.190
Imagine nowadays people talk big,

00:39:27.190 --> 00:39:29.190
but when it comes to action, they run away.

00:39:29.190 --> 00:39:31.190
This man, he spoke very big.

00:39:31.190 --> 00:39:33.190
When it came to action, he said okay

00:39:33.190 --> 00:39:34.190
and he went away.

00:39:34.190 --> 00:39:36.190
So Safwan ibn Umayyah had promised

00:39:36.190 --> 00:39:38.190
to look after the family and so on.

00:39:38.190 --> 00:39:40.190
When this Umayyah al-Jumahi

00:39:40.190 --> 00:39:42.190
got to Madinah Munawarah with his sword,

00:39:42.190 --> 00:39:44.190
Omar ibn Al-Khattab radiallahu anhu

00:39:44.190 --> 00:39:45.190
saw him with a few people

00:39:45.190 --> 00:39:47.190
and he says this man intends harm.

00:39:47.190 --> 00:39:49.190
So he caught him and brought him

00:39:49.190 --> 00:39:51.190
to Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:39:51.190 --> 00:39:53.190
And the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam said,

00:39:53.190 --> 00:39:55.190
leave him, leave him,

00:39:55.190 --> 00:39:56.190
release him, let me talk to him.

00:39:56.190 --> 00:39:58.190
He says, oh Umayyah al-Jumahi,

00:39:58.190 --> 00:39:59.190
why are you here?

00:39:59.190 --> 00:40:00.190
He says, I'm here for the captain.

00:40:00.190 --> 00:40:02.190
He said, but why did you bring a sword?

00:40:02.190 --> 00:40:03.190
Why are you here?

00:40:03.190 --> 00:40:04.190
Are you sure this is what it is?

00:40:04.190 --> 00:40:06.190
He says, no, I'm sure this is what it is.

00:40:06.190 --> 00:40:08.190
The Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam told him,

00:40:08.190 --> 00:40:10.190
no, Allah has informed me.

00:40:11.190 --> 00:40:13.190
You sat with Safwan ibn Umayyah

00:40:13.190 --> 00:40:14.190
in his house,

00:40:14.190 --> 00:40:15.190
and this was the discussion.

00:40:15.190 --> 00:40:17.190
And then you pick your sword up

00:40:17.190 --> 00:40:18.190
after he had said

00:40:18.190 --> 00:40:20.190
he will look after your affairs and your family

00:40:20.190 --> 00:40:22.190
and you came to Madinah Munawarah.

00:40:22.190 --> 00:40:23.190
This man was shocked.

00:40:23.190 --> 00:40:24.190
He said, wallahi,

00:40:24.190 --> 00:40:27.190
I have heard that you're a fortune teller,

00:40:27.190 --> 00:40:28.190
you're a magician,

00:40:28.190 --> 00:40:29.190
you are this, you are that.

00:40:29.190 --> 00:40:31.190
But this had happened in a way

00:40:31.190 --> 00:40:34.190
that nobody had seen it besides me and Safwan

00:40:34.190 --> 00:40:36.190
and I bear witness you are the messenger of Allah

00:40:36.190 --> 00:40:37.190
and I bear witness

00:40:37.190 --> 00:40:39.190
that there is none worthy of worship besides Allah.

00:40:39.190 --> 00:40:40.190
Subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:40:40.190 --> 00:40:41.190
He accepted Islam.

00:40:41.190 --> 00:40:43.190
Look at how he had come in

00:40:43.190 --> 00:40:45.190
with the bad intention

00:40:45.190 --> 00:40:46.190
and he accepted Islam

00:40:46.190 --> 00:40:48.190
and Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:40:48.190 --> 00:40:49.190
released his son as well.

00:40:49.190 --> 00:40:51.190
The two of them went back to Makkah al-Mukarramah.

00:40:51.190 --> 00:40:54.190
They did not allow him to leave Makkah thereafter

00:40:54.190 --> 00:40:55.190
to come back

00:40:55.190 --> 00:40:57.190
and he had to come very quietly.

00:40:57.190 --> 00:41:01.190
He came actually just before one of the battles.

00:41:01.190 --> 00:41:04.190
In fact, the time of Umrat al-Qadha,

00:41:04.190 --> 00:41:06.190
he had escaped to Madinah Munawarah,

00:41:06.190 --> 00:41:07.190
the same man.

00:41:07.190 --> 00:41:10.190
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant them mercy.

00:41:10.190 --> 00:41:12.190
Another man, very interesting,

00:41:12.190 --> 00:41:14.190
the uncle of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:41:14.190 --> 00:41:16.190
Two of his uncles were caught.

00:41:16.190 --> 00:41:17.190
He had come out.

00:41:17.190 --> 00:41:20.190
Now Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:41:20.190 --> 00:41:22.190
he told some of his companions that

00:41:22.190 --> 00:41:25.190
if you see Al-Abbas ibn Abdul Muttalib

00:41:25.190 --> 00:41:26.190
who is my uncle,

00:41:26.190 --> 00:41:29.190
don't kill him because he has come here

00:41:29.190 --> 00:41:32.190
being forced to come because of circumstances

00:41:32.190 --> 00:41:34.190
but he didn't want to fight us.

00:41:34.190 --> 00:41:37.190
He was the one who helped them to migrate to Madinah.

00:41:37.190 --> 00:41:41.190
He helped them strike the deal with the Ansar

00:41:41.190 --> 00:41:42.190
and so on in Mina.

00:41:42.190 --> 00:41:44.190
So this was the man.

00:41:44.190 --> 00:41:46.190
When he came,

00:41:46.190 --> 00:41:48.190
Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam saw him,

00:41:48.190 --> 00:41:52.190
Al-Abbas ibn Abdul Muttalib from amongst the captives.

00:41:52.190 --> 00:41:54.190
And Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam saw as well

00:41:54.190 --> 00:41:56.190
Aqeel ibn Abdul Muttalib,

00:41:56.190 --> 00:41:58.190
another uncle of his.

00:41:58.190 --> 00:42:01.190
And he says, you people need to pay the ransom.

00:42:01.190 --> 00:42:03.190
But you want us to pay ransom.

00:42:03.190 --> 00:42:04.190
We are related to you.

00:42:04.190 --> 00:42:06.190
No, you pay the ransom.

00:42:06.190 --> 00:42:08.190
If you are not going to pay the amount,

00:42:08.190 --> 00:42:09.190
nothing we can do.

00:42:09.190 --> 00:42:11.190
So Al-Abbas ibn Abdul Muttalib

00:42:11.190 --> 00:42:13.190
tells his nephew, all my nephew,

00:42:13.190 --> 00:42:15.190
you are going to make me poor.

00:42:15.190 --> 00:42:18.190
If I pay this amount that you are asking for,

00:42:18.190 --> 00:42:21.190
100 uqiya, which was a large amount,

00:42:21.190 --> 00:42:23.190
I will have nothing.

00:42:23.190 --> 00:42:25.190
And I'm going to be poor.

00:42:25.190 --> 00:42:26.190
I have nothing.

00:42:26.190 --> 00:42:28.190
The Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam says,

00:42:28.190 --> 00:42:30.190
you are telling a lie.

00:42:30.190 --> 00:42:32.190
Before you left for the war,

00:42:32.190 --> 00:42:36.190
you spoke to your wife, Umm al-Fadl.

00:42:36.190 --> 00:42:39.190
And you gave her a large sum.

00:42:39.190 --> 00:42:40.190
And you told her,

00:42:40.190 --> 00:42:42.190
I'm giving this to you because if I die,

00:42:42.190 --> 00:42:44.190
at least you can be wealthy.

00:42:44.190 --> 00:42:46.190
What about that sum?

00:42:46.190 --> 00:42:48.190
He said, who told you about that?

00:42:48.190 --> 00:42:50.190
It was a secret between me and her.

00:42:50.190 --> 00:42:51.190
Nobody knows about it.

00:42:51.190 --> 00:42:53.190
He says, Allah informed me.

00:42:53.190 --> 00:42:54.190
Subhanallah.

00:42:54.190 --> 00:42:57.190
May Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam grant us a deep understanding.

00:42:57.190 --> 00:42:58.190
Al-Abbas ibn Abdul Muttalib

00:42:58.190 --> 00:43:00.190
did not accept Islam at the time,

00:43:00.190 --> 00:43:01.190
but the amount had come in.

00:43:01.190 --> 00:43:03.190
He paid 100 uqiya

00:43:03.190 --> 00:43:05.190
and his brother Aqeel ibn Abdul Muttalib

00:43:05.190 --> 00:43:07.190
paid 80 uqiya

00:43:07.190 --> 00:43:09.190
and they had got the wealth

00:43:09.190 --> 00:43:12.190
that came in from Makkah to make that payment.

00:43:12.190 --> 00:43:16.190
He accepted Islam just before the victory of Makkah.

00:43:16.190 --> 00:43:18.190
That's when Al-Abbas ibn Abdul Muttalib

00:43:18.190 --> 00:43:20.190
came to Madinah Munawwara with his family.

00:43:20.190 --> 00:43:21.190
When the mushriks of Makkah

00:43:21.190 --> 00:43:23.190
were deciding what to do with the believers,

00:43:23.190 --> 00:43:25.190
he decided let's leave.

00:43:25.190 --> 00:43:27.190
He met the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam on the path.

00:43:27.190 --> 00:43:29.190
He joined the Muslims and he said,

00:43:29.190 --> 00:43:30.190
look, I bear witness.

00:43:30.190 --> 00:43:31.190
It's about time I came.

00:43:31.190 --> 00:43:34.190
May Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam grant us a deeper understanding.

00:43:34.190 --> 00:43:36.190
Another very, very interesting story

00:43:36.190 --> 00:43:39.190
is that of Abu Azzah al-Jumahi.

00:43:39.190 --> 00:43:41.190
He came to the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:43:41.190 --> 00:43:43.190
and he says, O Messenger sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:43:43.190 --> 00:43:46.190
I have nothing, no wealth,

00:43:46.190 --> 00:43:48.190
I have many children, they are in need of me.

00:43:48.190 --> 00:43:50.190
I came with the army, I fought you,

00:43:50.190 --> 00:43:52.190
and now I feel that I need to go back.

00:43:52.190 --> 00:43:55.190
I need to look after my people and my family and so on.

00:43:55.190 --> 00:43:57.190
And the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam studied his case.

00:43:57.190 --> 00:44:00.190
As we said, some of them were released without any payment

00:44:00.190 --> 00:44:01.190
because they were poor.

00:44:01.190 --> 00:44:03.190
This was one of them.

00:44:03.190 --> 00:44:05.190
He was released and he was told,

00:44:05.190 --> 00:44:06.190
okay, go back.

00:44:06.190 --> 00:44:07.190
You can go back to your people and so on.

00:44:07.190 --> 00:44:10.190
The man's name was Abu Azzah al-Jumahi

00:44:10.190 --> 00:44:12.190
and he was the one who the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:44:12.190 --> 00:44:13.190
had forgiven.

00:44:13.190 --> 00:44:15.190
And now when the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:44:15.190 --> 00:44:17.190
came to Madinah Munawwara,

00:44:17.190 --> 00:44:20.190
many of the people started entering the fold of Islam.

00:44:20.190 --> 00:44:24.190
Some of them, like Abdullah ibn Ubayy ibn Salool,

00:44:24.190 --> 00:44:26.190
they entered it because they saw

00:44:26.190 --> 00:44:28.190
the Muslims were mighty and powerful

00:44:28.190 --> 00:44:31.190
and they had seen that there is no way out.

00:44:31.190 --> 00:44:34.190
So now came the role of hypocrites.

00:44:34.190 --> 00:44:36.190
They were people who pretended to be Muslim

00:44:36.190 --> 00:44:37.190
and they were not.

00:44:37.190 --> 00:44:39.190
But the reason why they did it was

00:44:39.190 --> 00:44:41.190
to serve their own interests.

00:44:41.190 --> 00:44:43.190
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala safeguard us

00:44:43.190 --> 00:44:44.190
and grant us goodness.

00:44:44.190 --> 00:44:48.190
And may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala open our doors.

00:44:48.190 --> 00:44:52.190
I want to make mention of something very, very powerful.

00:44:52.190 --> 00:44:53.190
Very powerful.

00:44:53.190 --> 00:44:56.190
What was the rank of the people

00:44:56.190 --> 00:44:58.190
who took part in the Battle of Badr?

00:44:58.190 --> 00:45:00.190
It's important for us to know.

00:45:00.190 --> 00:45:05.190
They were from that day on known as Al-Badri.

00:45:05.190 --> 00:45:06.190
So after the name,

00:45:06.190 --> 00:45:09.190
you have a little title called Al-Badri.

00:45:09.190 --> 00:45:11.190
So if you hear Abu Mas'ud Al-Badri,

00:45:11.190 --> 00:45:14.190
it means that person took part in the Battle of Badr.

00:45:14.190 --> 00:45:16.190
He has a status higher than the others.

00:45:16.190 --> 00:45:18.190
When they came to Madinah Munawwara,

00:45:18.190 --> 00:45:21.190
there were some people who had

00:45:21.190 --> 00:45:23.190
not taken part in the war because

00:45:23.190 --> 00:45:27.190
they were given duties by Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:45:27.190 --> 00:45:29.190
Some of them, one of them in particular

00:45:29.190 --> 00:45:31.190
was granted the title of a person

00:45:31.190 --> 00:45:33.190
who took part in the Battle of Badr

00:45:33.190 --> 00:45:36.190
and his name was Uthman ibn Affan radiallahu anhu.

00:45:36.190 --> 00:45:38.190
He was married, very interestingly,

00:45:38.190 --> 00:45:40.190
to the daughter of Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:45:40.190 --> 00:45:43.190
who was divorced from the son of Abu Lahab,

00:45:43.190 --> 00:45:45.190
Ruqayyah radiallahu anhu.

00:45:45.190 --> 00:45:49.190
She was married to Uthman ibn Affan

00:45:49.190 --> 00:45:52.190
after she was divorced from the son of Abu Lahab

00:45:52.190 --> 00:45:54.190
because when Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:45:54.190 --> 00:45:59.190
in Makkah had started spreading Islam,

00:45:59.190 --> 00:46:02.190
Abu Lahab told his sons,

00:46:02.190 --> 00:46:04.190
two of them were married to two of the daughters

00:46:04.190 --> 00:46:06.190
of Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:46:06.190 --> 00:46:09.190
Ruqayyah and Um Kulthum.

00:46:09.190 --> 00:46:12.190
So Abu Lahab told them divorce these two

00:46:12.190 --> 00:46:13.190
and send them back home.

00:46:13.190 --> 00:46:14.190
That's exactly what they did.

00:46:14.190 --> 00:46:16.190
This is my enemy, send them home.

00:46:16.190 --> 00:46:18.190
So these mushriks of Makkah,

00:46:18.190 --> 00:46:20.190
they had divorced the two daughters.

00:46:20.190 --> 00:46:23.190
Uthman ibn Affan radiallahu anhu married one.

00:46:23.190 --> 00:46:26.190
Just after the Battle of Badr,

00:46:26.190 --> 00:46:28.190
she lost her life, Ruqayyah,

00:46:28.190 --> 00:46:30.190
binti Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:46:30.190 --> 00:46:32.190
And this was also a very sad day

00:46:32.190 --> 00:46:35.190
because Uthman ibn Affan was told

00:46:35.190 --> 00:46:37.190
not to take part in the battle

00:46:37.190 --> 00:46:39.190
because he needed to look after his wife.

00:46:39.190 --> 00:46:40.190
His wife passed away

00:46:40.190 --> 00:46:42.190
and the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam told him,

00:46:42.190 --> 00:46:44.190
don't worry, you marry the other daughter of mine.

00:46:44.190 --> 00:46:45.190
Her name was Um Kulthum.

00:46:46.190 --> 00:46:47.190
And this is why he is called

00:46:47.190 --> 00:46:50.190
Uthman dhinnurayn.

00:46:50.190 --> 00:46:51.190
He had married the two Nurs,

00:46:51.190 --> 00:46:52.190
the two points of light,

00:46:52.190 --> 00:46:54.190
which means two of the daughters

00:46:54.190 --> 00:46:56.190
of the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:46:56.190 --> 00:46:58.190
they were both married to Uthman ibn Affan,

00:46:58.190 --> 00:47:01.190
Uthman dhinnurayn radiallahu anhu jami'an.

00:47:01.190 --> 00:47:02.190
May Allah be pleased with all of them.

00:47:02.190 --> 00:47:04.190
As for Al-Aas ibn al-Rabiya,

00:47:04.190 --> 00:47:06.190
we said he was married to Zainab

00:47:06.190 --> 00:47:08.190
binti Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:47:08.190 --> 00:47:10.190
Abu Lahab went to him and told him,

00:47:10.190 --> 00:47:12.190
my two sons have divorced

00:47:12.190 --> 00:47:14.190
the two daughters of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:47:14.190 --> 00:47:17.190
You also go and divorce Zainab,

00:47:17.190 --> 00:47:19.190
the daughter of Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:47:19.190 --> 00:47:21.190
Do you know what he said in Makkah

00:47:21.190 --> 00:47:22.190
in the early days?

00:47:22.190 --> 00:47:23.190
And this is one of the things

00:47:23.190 --> 00:47:24.190
that was remembered the day

00:47:24.190 --> 00:47:27.190
he was granted freedom from captivity.

00:47:27.190 --> 00:47:29.190
He said to Abu Lahab,

00:47:29.190 --> 00:47:31.190
you can do what you want,

00:47:31.190 --> 00:47:33.190
I'm not going to divorce this wife of mine.

00:47:33.190 --> 00:47:36.190
I love her and she is one of the best of the women.

00:47:36.190 --> 00:47:38.190
And if you were to give me

00:47:38.190 --> 00:47:40.190
any one of the women of Quraysh in her place,

00:47:40.190 --> 00:47:42.190
I would never release her.

00:47:42.190 --> 00:47:43.190
They wouldn't be able to do

00:47:43.190 --> 00:47:44.190
justice to her level.

00:47:44.190 --> 00:47:46.190
So he really loved his wife.

00:47:46.190 --> 00:47:48.190
And this is why Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:47:48.190 --> 00:47:51.190
brought him just before Yawm al-Fatih,

00:47:51.190 --> 00:47:53.190
the day when the victory of Makkah happened

00:47:53.190 --> 00:47:55.190
and the wife and husband were united

00:47:55.190 --> 00:47:56.190
once again as Muslimin.

00:47:56.190 --> 00:47:58.190
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us

00:47:58.190 --> 00:47:59.190
a deep understanding.

00:47:59.190 --> 00:48:02.190
So we were making mention of a Badri.

00:48:02.190 --> 00:48:04.190
Badri being a person who took part

00:48:04.190 --> 00:48:05.190
in the Battle of Badr.

00:48:05.190 --> 00:48:08.190
But at some stage later on

00:48:08.190 --> 00:48:11.190
when the Muslims were preparing to conquer Makkah,

00:48:11.190 --> 00:48:12.190
to march onto Makkah,

00:48:12.190 --> 00:48:13.190
many years later,

00:48:13.190 --> 00:48:15.190
one of the people who took part

00:48:15.190 --> 00:48:17.190
in the Battle of Badr made a mistake.

00:48:17.190 --> 00:48:18.190
What was his mistake?

00:48:18.190 --> 00:48:20.190
He was worried because there were

00:48:20.190 --> 00:48:21.190
thousands of Muslims preparing

00:48:21.190 --> 00:48:22.190
to march onto Makkah.

00:48:22.190 --> 00:48:24.190
And he had some interests in Makkah

00:48:24.190 --> 00:48:27.190
and members who were members of his family.

00:48:27.190 --> 00:48:29.190
He wrote a letter for them and he sent it.

00:48:29.190 --> 00:48:30.190
He sent it quietly to say,

00:48:30.190 --> 00:48:32.190
this is what is the plan of the Muslims.

00:48:32.190 --> 00:48:34.190
His name was

00:48:34.190 --> 00:48:36.190
Hatib ibn Abi Balta'ah,

00:48:36.190 --> 00:48:39.190
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us

00:48:39.190 --> 00:48:40.190
all a high rank.

00:48:40.190 --> 00:48:42.190
Hatib ibn Abi Balta'ah made a mistake.

00:48:42.190 --> 00:48:43.190
He wrote this letter

00:48:43.190 --> 00:48:46.190
and Allah had informed Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:48:46.190 --> 00:48:47.190
they intercepted the letter

00:48:47.190 --> 00:48:48.190
at a certain point inshallah

00:48:48.190 --> 00:48:49.190
we will get to that

00:48:49.190 --> 00:48:51.190
when we discuss that battle.

00:48:51.190 --> 00:48:52.190
And thereafter,

00:48:52.190 --> 00:48:54.190
some of the Sahaba got up

00:48:54.190 --> 00:48:56.190
and they wanted to execute Hatib.

00:48:56.190 --> 00:48:58.190
They told Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:48:58.190 --> 00:49:00.190
can we beat this hypocrite?

00:49:00.190 --> 00:49:01.190
The Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam says,

00:49:01.190 --> 00:49:03.190
what are you talking about?

00:49:03.190 --> 00:49:04.190
Do you know he took part

00:49:04.190 --> 00:49:05.190
in the Battle of Badr?

00:49:05.190 --> 00:49:06.190
How do you know?

00:49:06.190 --> 00:49:08.190
Allah looked at the hearts of the people

00:49:08.190 --> 00:49:10.190
who took part in the Battle of Badr

00:49:10.190 --> 00:49:11.190
and told them,

00:49:11.190 --> 00:49:12.190
do as you please from this day,

00:49:12.190 --> 00:49:15.190
I have forgiven you completely.

00:49:15.190 --> 00:49:16.190
Subhanallah.

00:49:16.190 --> 00:49:18.190
That was the rank of the people of Badr.

00:49:18.190 --> 00:49:21.190
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says,

00:49:21.190 --> 00:49:24.190
He looked at their hearts on that day

00:49:24.190 --> 00:49:25.190
and He told them,

00:49:25.190 --> 00:49:27.190
do as you please from this day.

00:49:27.190 --> 00:49:28.190
Subhanallah.

00:49:28.190 --> 00:49:29.190
That was the rank of the people of Badr.

00:49:29.190 --> 00:49:32.190
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says,

00:49:32.190 --> 00:49:34.190
He looked at their hearts on that day

00:49:34.190 --> 00:49:35.190
and told them,

00:49:35.190 --> 00:49:36.190
do as you please,

00:49:36.190 --> 00:49:37.190
I have forgiven you.

00:49:37.190 --> 00:49:38.190
Subhanallah.

00:49:38.190 --> 00:49:40.190
And this is why Hatib was excused.

00:49:40.190 --> 00:49:41.190
The Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:49:41.190 --> 00:49:43.190
did not punish him at all.

00:49:43.190 --> 00:49:45.190
Later on the same Hatib,

00:49:45.190 --> 00:49:49.190
someone spoke about Hatib ibn Abi Balta'ah.

00:49:49.190 --> 00:49:51.190
And the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam says,

00:49:51.190 --> 00:49:53.190
how can you say he is a hypocrite

00:49:53.190 --> 00:49:56.190
when he took part not only in Badr

00:49:56.190 --> 00:49:58.190
but even in Hudaibiyah?

00:49:58.190 --> 00:49:59.190
Allahu Akbar.

00:49:59.190 --> 00:50:00.190
Even in Hudaibiyah he took part.

00:50:00.190 --> 00:50:02.190
Don't call him a hypocrite.

00:50:02.190 --> 00:50:04.190
And this is why the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam says,

00:50:15.190 --> 00:50:18.190
Don't ever speak bad about those companions of mine.

00:50:18.190 --> 00:50:21.190
Don't speak bad about my companions

00:50:21.190 --> 00:50:23.190
because I swear by Allah,

00:50:23.190 --> 00:50:29.190
if you had to spend gold worth the Mount Uhud,

00:50:29.190 --> 00:50:32.190
it would never ever equate even one hand

00:50:32.190 --> 00:50:36.190
that they had spent or even half of their handful.

00:50:36.190 --> 00:50:38.190
Theirs was much more in value

00:50:38.190 --> 00:50:40.190
than whatever you can do.

00:50:40.190 --> 00:50:42.190
So don't ever talk bad about the companions

00:50:42.190 --> 00:50:44.190
not a single one of them.

00:50:44.190 --> 00:50:46.190
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us love

00:50:46.190 --> 00:50:48.190
for the companions.

00:50:48.190 --> 00:50:50.190
When the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:50:50.190 --> 00:50:52.190
got to Madinah Munawwarah,

00:50:52.190 --> 00:50:54.190
something else happened there.

00:50:54.190 --> 00:50:56.190
There was a lot of noise

00:50:56.190 --> 00:50:59.190
being made by some of the people of the book,

00:50:59.190 --> 00:51:01.190
Banu Qaynuqa in particular

00:51:01.190 --> 00:51:03.190
and some of the hypocrites.

00:51:03.190 --> 00:51:04.190
They were trying to harm

00:51:04.190 --> 00:51:06.190
Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam's

00:51:06.190 --> 00:51:08.190
the unity of the Muslims.

00:51:08.190 --> 00:51:09.190
They were trying to harm it.

00:51:09.190 --> 00:51:12.190
And they had broken the treaty

00:51:12.190 --> 00:51:14.190
that they had had with the Muslims

00:51:14.190 --> 00:51:16.190
in a few ways.

00:51:16.190 --> 00:51:19.190
One of them was as follows.

00:51:19.190 --> 00:51:22.190
In the market place of Banu Qaynuqa,

00:51:22.190 --> 00:51:24.190
one of the Muslim women

00:51:24.190 --> 00:51:26.190
was sitting

00:51:26.190 --> 00:51:29.190
and she had covered herself completely.

00:51:29.190 --> 00:51:33.190
And one of the people of Banu Qaynuqa

00:51:33.190 --> 00:51:36.190
mockingly, as she was sitting,

00:51:36.190 --> 00:51:39.190
he sewed the bottom of her dress

00:51:39.190 --> 00:51:41.190
to the top of her dress

00:51:41.190 --> 00:51:42.190
and he put a stitch

00:51:42.190 --> 00:51:43.190
and he carried on quietly

00:51:43.190 --> 00:51:45.190
while she did not notice.

00:51:45.190 --> 00:51:47.190
So because she was sitting,

00:51:47.190 --> 00:51:49.190
she didn't know what had happened.

00:51:49.190 --> 00:51:50.190
When she got up,

00:51:50.190 --> 00:51:52.190
part of her leg showed

00:51:53.190 --> 00:51:55.190
they laughed at her

00:51:55.190 --> 00:51:57.190
because now it was stuck.

00:51:57.190 --> 00:51:58.190
When that happened,

00:51:58.190 --> 00:52:00.190
some of the Muslims got up

00:52:00.190 --> 00:52:03.190
and they attacked the man who did it.

00:52:03.190 --> 00:52:05.190
And sadly, it resulted in his death.

00:52:05.190 --> 00:52:07.190
When that happened,

00:52:07.190 --> 00:52:09.190
some of the people of Banu Qaynuqa

00:52:09.190 --> 00:52:11.190
got up and they started fighting

00:52:11.190 --> 00:52:12.190
with the Muslims.

00:52:12.190 --> 00:52:15.190
News got to Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:52:15.190 --> 00:52:16.190
that this is what they did

00:52:16.190 --> 00:52:19.190
to one believing woman.

00:52:19.190 --> 00:52:20.190
And inshallah,

00:52:20.190 --> 00:52:22.190
tomorrow we will see how he retaliated

00:52:22.190 --> 00:52:24.190
sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:52:24.190 --> 00:52:25.190
until we meet again.

00:52:25.190 --> 00:52:26.190
We say,

00:52:26.190 --> 00:52:27.190
wa sallallahu wa sallam wa baraka

00:52:27.190 --> 00:52:28.190
ala nabina Muhammad

00:52:28.190 --> 00:52:29.190
subhanallahi wa bi hamdi

00:52:29.190 --> 00:52:31.190
subhanaka allahum wa bi hamdik

00:52:31.190 --> 00:52:33.190
nashhadu alla ilaha illa anta

00:52:33.190 --> 00:52:35.190
astaghfiruka wa natubu ilayh
